entries.femaleVariant: So what now?
Sorry, but could we talk, please? Just a minute, promise.
About what?
Sure. What about?
Not what, but who. Razor.
My dad fought him once. A long time ago, when Razor just got started.
My dad fell in the third round, the ref stopped the fight... But Razor didn't stop. Three more minutes he beat my dad. He survived, but...
I can imagine. Where's this story going?
That's why I'm here.
Leave me alone.
That's why I'm here, little girl.
Get lost, kid. Go.
Fuck you, too! Fuck you!
Aha! The star of the hour! Great to see you, V!
So... what now?
"What now?" she says, hah! The title match! You go up against Razor Hughes. Heard of him, haven't you?
entries.maleVariant: "What now?" he says, hah! The title match! You go up against Razor Hughes. Heard of him, haven't you?

entries.femaleVariant: Hey, César.
Hey, Rhino.
Yo, Rhino. See you're keepin' busy.
entries.maleVariant: Yo, Rhino. I see you're keepin' busy.

entries.femaleVariant: I'm all ears.
No thanks.
I'll pass.
Hey, hey... You don't even know what it is yet.
Hit me with it.
No, not here. Too many ears around. Let's step aside.
What I'm gonna say, it has to be between us, all right?
Well, V, I'll get right to it... I know sports oughta be fair, but life sure ain't. I'm not wrong, am I?
I'll do it.
OK, I'll do it.
Everyone's got a price. You can't afford mine.
C'mon, let's get back before people start to talk.
All right, so... Are you two ready to fight?
Only one round.
What?
Let's do it.
May the best brawler win!
[Get up and start fight] Ready.
Let's start this thing.
I'm ready.
Good... Ladies and Gentlemen! Night Citizens! It's time for our heavyweight bout!
Go on! To your corners!
You two ready? At the gong!
Facing each other tonight, we have... Razor Hughes and V! Let's hear it!
Call it now! This fight's over!
The title and prize belong to Razor Hughes! Your champion!
Hey, easy, you two! The fight's over!
A pleasure to beat you. Maybe you're lookin' earn extra eddies as a punchin' bag? Maybe I chain you to the ceilin', finish what I started?
V, step aside a minute. We gotta talk.
I'm glad you found reason. Here, as promised. Your take.
Nice work. It looked natural, nobody seems to suspect a thing.
Really feel I earned every enny here. But God, that Razor... what a piece of shit.
He is, no doubt. But he is where he is and he has what he has.
Victory and the prize belong to V! Your champion!
You'd be wise to. Don't think you could take another beating.
You think this's how it ends? Th-that I just let you outta my grip?
I knew this would happen. Only the best could beat me.
Hah! Now THAT is boxing!
Yeah, yeah. It went perfect and Razor lost... How much? Uh, tons? A few thousand at least!
Actor? What're you talking about?
Haha! What can I say, I'm a good actor!
You're a sharp kid.
Hah. Quite the sharp little con artist.
Wait, no, uh, I-I can explain everything...
Wait, wait... "actor"? So you pulled that whole father story outta your ass?
Ehhh... Sorry, don't know what you're talking about. Gotta go!
Ugh... Could've figured.
Chin up. You're lucky you still got a pulse.
<kiroshi l="creo" o="Ale nan lòt bò gwo sal la. Yap tann nou." t="They are waiting for you over there. There, other side of the room." b="" a=""/>
Hey, how're you two?
I'm not twins! It's just me!
Well if it isn't my favorite twins in Night City. 'Sup, fellas?
I'm not twins! It's just me!
Congrats! Well done.
Really, congrats!
That was a dirty move, V. Damn dirty.
What are you doing here, Vik?
Vik? What're you doin' here?
Whaddaya mean? I came to see the fight of the year. Everybody on the street's buzzin' about it.
Don't let me down now, you hear?
You threw the fight, didn't you?
That's bush league, V. Bush league.
Slick work, V.
Hail, César. Shouldn't you be puttin' up a cradle or somethin'?
Due date's tomorrow. I got time.
Next time I'm wipin' the floor with you. You'll see.
Anyway... I'm fine, thank you.
Nowhere. It's finished. Like my old life. Like my life now...
Just... I want Razor punished for what he did. I need him to know how he made my dad feel.
Th-thanks... I'll cross my fingers for you.
I can guess. So again – I'll pass. I fight to win. Period.
entries.maleVariant: Yeah, I can guess. So again – I'll pass. I fight to win. Period.

entries.femaleVariant: OK, Jesus, be that way.
Cut the drama. What's this about?
No way. I'm out.
Hah! Knew from the start you have good instincts.
It's your ass gettin' beat, V. Bad move, but it's your call.
One round – all it's gonna take for you to kiss my feet and beg for mercy.
Right, ahem... Shall we?
This ain't over 'tween us. We'll meet again. Tomorrow, next year... This definitely ain't the last.
See ya 'round then. I suggest you train in the meantime.
Depends. Do I gotta listen to this bullshit the whole time, or do you never shut up?
Thanks.
Shove it.
Shove the money up your ass.
But... what? V, what's wrong?
Don't dwell on it. At the end of the day, all that matters is the eddies. And you're sittin' comfy now.
No need. Earn what ya can, how ya can.
I sign autographs after the fight.
Me, I prefer to get drunk after a win.
Wait, wait, wait, hol' up. You're V? Pff.
Why do you fight the amateur circuit?
Won't be that easy.
I ain't your typical ring fodder.
What's a heavyweight champ doin' in the bush leagues? Money problems at home?
On the contrary. I got so much, I dunno what to do with it. That's my problem.
Ya see, I started in the mud an' shit. Now I climbed too high an' my fans can feel it.
I gotta show 'em I'm still a scrappy street kid at heart. And you... well, you're just the wrong place, wrong time.
"A scrappy street kid..." What, who sits his ass on leather in the VIP area?
What cyberware you got?
What's your chrome? Hausstocks? Ichors?
Seriously? That mass-market bullshit?
V, hey. How're your spirits before the fight?
But listen, I'll be honest... It don't look too good for you. But uh, maybe that's better, y'know?
He use actual razors?
I've seen posters.
We met.
Nope. He got a shaving cream sponsor?
entries.maleVariant: No. He got a shaving cream sponsor?

entries.femaleVariant: Think I've seen posters. He's a pro boxer, right?
entries.maleVariant: I think I've seen posters. He's a pro boxer, right?

entries.femaleVariant: Met him, actually. Don't know what's bigger, his biceps or his ego.
Never thought I'd see him here because, you know, he's a star athlete with elite corpo sponsors...
But then his agent tells us it's a good PR move for him. Razor returning to his roots and all that, prove he's still a kid from the streets.
Do I even have a shot?
Hah, a good question. You're good, V, very good. But this guy... he's a machine.
Carbon fiber, titanium bones, hydraulic joints... all optimized by Night City's best bioengineers.
If Razor's winnin' anyway... maybe you're lookin'... earn a little somethin' on it?
Razor's manager wants his star to shine. He wants the whole city to hear about the hurt he put on this ring.
My point... Pull some punches, forget to put that guard up sometimes... Then get comfortable on the ground.
How much?
A lot. More than you'd earn by winnin'.
His gut! Hit him in the gut!
Keep your guard up! Or you'll hit the deck!
Good! Keep the pressure till he breaks!
Ya got 'em staggering! Just gotta land a few more!
Had a good coach in my corner.
entries.maleVariant: I had a good coach in my corner.

entries.femaleVariant: I lost, that's what I'm tellin' you!
The fuck you mean "backin' out"? All of 'em? You fuckin' shittin' me...
No, I don't know "what the fuck now"! Ain't you the goddamn manager?! It's your job!
[Sit]
Mhm. Let's get it.
If you're goin' anywhere after the fight, it's the ER. To collect whatever's left of ya.
Don't make me laugh. One knock to the jaw and you'll curl up in a tiny ball.
Not the most convincing underdog story I've heard.
My chrome's stricly prototype, ain't even out yet. Think of me as testin' ground for the corps... and you my guinea pig.
My record in the ring's a healthy forty-seven W's, zero losses. With twenty by knockout.
And you look like a twenty first if ever I seen one.
He is THE boxer! You had your head buried in the sand?
Very fuckin' funny. He's a three-time heavyweight champion!
And you're surprised? He's a three-time heavyweight champ!
I dunno, maybe Viktor'll have some tips or tricks...
Vik's here?
What, you think he'd miss an occasion like this?
Shitty.
Ready to go.
Honestly? I feel sick.
Good. But my knuckles are itchin'.
How do you mean?
Yeah, he's a tough matchup. But y'know, no one's unbeatable. Even him.
Hah! You won't get far in this sport without confidence.
But y'know, positive thinking's only gonna get you so far against an opponent like Razor.
The guy's a tank. Seriously. Nanofiber RealSkinn, shock absorbers... You could knock him on the head with a meat mallet and he wouldn't even flinch.
'Preciate the pep talk.
Hold on now, I'm not done. He's got a weakness. Had some abdominal muscles swapped out a week ago and they haven't taken to him fully just yet.
You hit him there, it's gonna hurt. A lot.
Thanks, Vik. Keep it in mind.
entries.maleVariant: Thanks, Vik. I'll keep it in mind.

entries.femaleVariant: [Sit and wait]
[Sit]
[Stand]
